# React + TypeScript Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Vite or Next.js as build tool
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- React Query / SWR for data fetching
- Zustand or Context API for state

## Code Style
- Functional components only — no class components
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use `const` arrow functions for components: `const MyComponent = () => {}`
- Props interfaces must be explicitly typed — never use `any`
- Co-locate types with the component file unless shared

## File & Folder Conventions
- Component files: PascalCase (`UserCard.tsx`)
- Hook files: camelCase starting with `use` (`useAuth.ts`)
- Utility files: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`)
- Each component in its own folder with index barrel export

## React Patterns
- Custom hooks for all business logic — keep components presentational
- `useCallback` / `useMemo` only when profiling shows it helps
- Error boundaries for async components
- Lazy-load routes with `React.lazy` and `Suspense`

## TypeScript
- Strict mode required (`"strict": true` in tsconfig)
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- No `!` non-null assertions — handle undefined explicitly
- Import types with `import type { Foo }` syntax

## Testing
- Vitest + React Testing Library
- Test behavior, not implementation
- One describe block per component
- Name tests: "should <expected behavior> when <condition>"
